{"id":118,"parent_id":114,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":118,"title":"Romans 4-5: Faith in Jesus Christ Is the Key to Overcoming Sin","subtitle":"","short_title":"Romans 4-5: Faith in Jesus Christ Is the Key to Overcoming Sin","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin"},[".heading",{"id":"head5","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.head5"},["h1","Romans 4–5"],[".subtitle","Faith in Jesus Christ Is the Key to Overcoming Sin"],[".intro","Consider for a moment your personal weaknesses. Have you ever wondered how you could better overcome the temptations you face? What might you do to improve your relationship with the Lord and have more power to live righteously?"],[".intro","Paul reminded the Jewish Christians that Abraham did not have the law of Moses, yet he was an example of faith and lived a righteous life. The law of Moses was added later because of disobedience. The children of Israel needed to learn to obey that law before they could be trusted with a higher law. Paul taught the people that in every dispensation faith in the Lord Jesus Christ, not the law of Moses, was the key to overcoming sin and living righteously."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.f9"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4"},"Romans 4"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Justified by works"],"(v. 2)"],["td","False idea that one’s good acts alone are sufficient to overcome sin and obtain salvation"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Impute, imputed, imputeth"],"(vv. 6, 8, 11, 22, 23–24)"],["td","Count, counted, counts"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.2-5"},"Romans 4:2–5"],"—Additional Insight from the Joseph Smith Translation"],["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p40"},"The Joseph Smith Translation helps us understand that if we depend on our obedience to the law to save us, we will only get what we have earned by ourselves and no more. But if we have faith in God and try to be obedient, our faith will be counted as righteousness and our sins will be forgiven."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.9-12"},"Romans 4:9–12"],"—What Did Paul Mean by This Discussion on Circumcision?"],["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p41"},"The word",["span.emphasis","circumcision"],"is used here as a symbol of the law of Moses. Many Jews felt they were the only ones who could be called righteous because only they observed the law of Moses. Paul reminded them that God called Abraham righteous because of his faith long before the law was given to Moses."],[".figure",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.f10"},["p"],["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/5"},"Romans 5"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Commendeth"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Shows, exhibits"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Reconciled to God"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Returned to God’s favor"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Sin is not imputed"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Are not charged with sin"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Similitude"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Likeness"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Abounded"],"(vv. 15, 20)"],["td","Overflowed"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/5.12-21"},"Romans 5:12–21"],"—“By the Offence of One … By the Righteousness of One”"],["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p47"},"Through the transgression of one (Adam), sin and death entered the world. By the mission of another (Jesus Christ) we can receive the gift of God and be saved from sin and death (see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/15.21-22"},"1 Corinthians 15:21–22"],")."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p48"},"Do activities A and B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4"},"Romans 4–5"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Abraham, an Example of Faith"],[".",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-114-1.gif"}]],["p.para",{"id":"p49","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p49"},"Paul used the example of Abraham to show that faith in God is the beginning of righteousness. Abraham was called righteous even before the law of Moses was given. Write the following sentences in your notebook and complete them as you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.9-25"},"Romans 4:9–25"],":"],[".figure",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.f12"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Abraham was",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.11"},"v. 11"],")."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","The promises to Abraham came as a result of his",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.13"},"v. 13"],")."]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","God’s promise comes as a",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/10.16"},"v. 16"],")."]],["li",["span.label","4."],["p.para","Jesus Christ died for our",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/10.25"},"v. 25"],")."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Write Your Testimony"],["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.p54"},"After reading",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/5.12-21"},"Romans 5:12–21"],", write your testimony of Jesus Christ and of His role as your Savior."]]],[".",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-4-5-faith-in-jesus-christ-is-the-key-to-overcoming-sin.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-114-2.gif"}]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
